  "response": "Here are some examples of instinctive behaviors in humans and animals:\n\nHumans:\n1. Newborn reflexes (sucking, rooting)\n2. Fear response\n3. Maternal/parental bonding and protection\n4. Fight or flight response\n5. Basic survival instincts like seeking food and water\n\nAnimals:\n1. Migration patterns (birds, salmon)\n2. Web spinning by spiders\n3. Bee communication and hive organization\n4. Hibernation in bears and other mammals\n5. Hunting/predatory behaviors\n6. Animal courtship and mating rituals\n7. Nest building\n8. Self-defense mechanisms\n\nThese behaviors are typically:\n- Genetically programmed\n- Performed without learning\n- Consistent across species members\n- Essential for survival and reproduction\n- Often triggered automatically by specific stimuli\n\nInstinctive behaviors help organisms respond quickly to environmental challenges and improve their chances of survival.",
